XML code completion adds closing tag when fully typing a self-closed tag Start typing {{<label (e.g.="" a="" alloy="" and="" editor="" if="" in="" now="" sec="" studio="" the="" then="" type="" view).="" wait="" xml="" you="" {{="" }}="">}} everything is OK. You have created a self-closed {{<label></label>}} tag with no problem.

But the following cases don't:

* Type {{<label></label>}} without stopping and you'll get {{<label></label>&gt;</label>}}
* Type {{<label foo="bar"></label>}} and you'll get {{<label foo="bar">&gt;</label>}}

This can be very irritating when typing lots of self closed-tags, e.g. Alloy view elements.

